# HTML
 
HTML, OR THE HYPER TEXT MARKUP LANGUAGE, IS THE LANGAUGE OF THE WORLD WIDE WEB!  

HTML IS USES "TAGS" TO CREATE "ELEMENTS" IN THE BROWSER, WHICH GET RENDERED INTO WHAT YOU ACTUALLY SEE ON YOUR SCREEN WHEN YOU LOOK AT THE WEB!

TAGS ARE MADE OF A PAIR OF ANGLE BRACKETS AND LOOK LIKE THIS:

```
<P>THIS IS A PARAGRAPH!</P>
``` 

IF YOU WANT TO SEE THE CODE FOR  ANY GIVEN WEB PAGE IN [FIREFOX](https://www.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/) YOU CAN JUST USE CONTROL U AND YOU WILL SEE THE CODE!

LOOK AT ALL THE CODE ON DIFFERENT WEB PAGES!

LOOK AT THE HTML!

AND THEN YOU CAN LEARN ALL ABOUT HTML IN THE LINKS BELOW:

 - [WIKIPEDIA](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTML)
 - [MOZILLA DEVELOPER NETWORK](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML)
 - [W3SCHOOLS TUTORIAL](https://www.w3schools.com/html/)
 